<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-20092] camel-core - ScheduledPollConsumer should reset error count when greedy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-20092</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have had the following scenario happen to us on a SQS consumer with greedy=true:&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;poll 1: fails with exception, causing error count to increase to 1 (due to sqs problem)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;poll 2: successfully poll, and since greedy, continues with the next poll. This continued for 1 hour as the queue it polled from had many messages&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the error count wasn&apos;t updated, then our readiness check remained DOWN for a full hour even though the application actually processed messages of the queue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
